tists]]\n[[Category:Matador Records artists]]\n[[Category:Scat Records artists]]\n[[Category:Musical groups from Dayton, Ohio]]\n[[Category:Lo-fi music groups]]\n[[Category:Musical groups reestablished in 2010]]\n[[Category:Musical groups disestablished in 2014]]\n[[Category:1983 establishments in Ohio]]\n", "name_user": "JohnTheCoolChild", "label": "safe", "comment": "I EDITED SOME STUFF", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guided_by_Voices"}
{"title_page": "Wu Yundong", "text_new": "{{BLP primary sources|BLP=yes|date=July 2011}}\n{{Chinese name|[[Wu (surname)|Wu]]}}\n\n'''Wu Yundong''' ({{zh|s=\u5434\u4e91\u4e1c}}) is a Chinese chemist. He is a theoretical organic chemist based in the [[Hong Kong University of Science and Technology]] and holds a concurrent position in [[Peking University]]. He was born 10 May 1957 in [[Liyang]], [[Jiangsu]], [[China]]. He graduated with a BS from [[Lanzhou University]] in 1982 and received his PhD in 1986 from the [[University of Pittsburgh]], working with [[Kendall N. Houk]] in computational organic chemistry. He went on to become a research associate in [[University of California Los Angeles]] from 1989 to 1992, before beginning his independent research career in [[Hong Kong]].\n\nProfessor Wu has received numerous awards in his career; in December 2005, he was elected as an Academician of the prestigious [[Chinese Academy of Sciences]]. His research interest focuses mainly on the elucidation of reaction mechanisms, protein-protein interactions/aggregations ([[Alzheimer's disease]] etc.) and conformational features of natural and unnatural peptides.\n\n==External links==\n# [http://www.chem.pku.edu.cn/page/ITCC/faculty/YdWu/ Curriculum Vitae from Peking University College of Chemistry ]\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Members of the Chinese Academy of Sciences (2005)}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wu, Yundong}}\n[[Category:1957 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Chongqing University faculty]]\n[[Category:Computational chemists]]\n[[Category:Educators from Changzhou]]\n[[Category:Hong Kong University of Science and Technology faculty]]\n[[Category:Lanzhou University alumni]]\n[[Category:Members of the Chinese Academy of Sciences]]\n[[Category:Organic chemists]]\n[[Category:Peking University faculty]]\n[[Category:People from Liyang]]\n[[Category:Scientists from Changzhou]]\n[[Category:University of Pittsburgh alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{BLP primary sources|BLP=yes|date=July 2011}}\n{{Chinese name|[[Wu (surname)|Wu]]}}\n\n'''Wu Yundong''' ({{zh|s=\u5434\u4e91\u4e1c}}) is a Chinese chemist. He is a theoretical organic chemist based in the [[Hong Kong University of Science and Technology]] and holds a concurrent position in [[Peking University]]. He was born 10 May 1957 in [[Liyang]], [[Jiangsu]], [[China]]. He graduated with a BS from [[Lanzhou University]] in 1982 and received his PhD in 1986 from the [[University of Pittsburgh]], working with [[Kendall N. Houk]] in computational organic chemistry. He went on to become a research associate in [[University of California Los Angeles]] from 1989 to 1992, before beginning his independent research career in [[Hong Kong]].\n\nProfessor Wu has received numerous awards in his career; in December 2005, he was elected as an Academician of the prestigious [[Chinese Academy of Sciences]]. His research interest focuses mainly on the elucidation of reaction mechanisms, protein-protein interactions/aggregations ([[Alzheimer's disease]] etc.) and conformational features of natural and unnatural peptides.\n\n==External links==\n# [http://www.chem.pku.edu.cn/page/ITCC/faculty/YdWu/ Curriculum Vitae from Peking University College of Chemistry ]\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2010}}\n{{Members of the Chinese Academy of Sciences (2005)}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wu, Yundong}}\n[[Category:1957 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Chongqing University faculty]]\n[[Category:Computational chemists]]\n[[Category:Educators from Changzhou]\n[[Category:Hong Kong University of Science and Technology faculty]]\n[[Category:Lanzhou University alumni]]\n[[Category:Members of the Chinese Academy of Sciences]]\n[[Category:Organic chemists]]\n[[Category:Peking University faculty]]\n[[Category:People from Liyang]]\n[[Category:Scientists from Changzhou]]\n[[Category:University of Pittsburgh alumni]]\n", "name_user": "Rich Farmbrough", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:Update date format tag", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wu_Yundong"}
{"title_page": "The Boundary (2020 film)", "text_new": "{{unreferenced|date=March 2020}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = The Boundary\n| film name      = \u0997\u09a3\u09cd\u09a1\u09bf\n| image          = Gondi.jpg\n| caption        = The Boundary\n| director       = [[Fakhrul Arefeen Khan]]\n| producers      = [[Fakhrul Arefeen Khan]] & [[Israt Sultana]]\n| writer         = [[Fakhrul Arefeen Khan]]\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Sabyasachi Chakrabarty]]\n* [[Suborna Mustafa]]\n* [[Aparna Ghose]] \n* [[Maznun Mizan]] \n}}\n| music          = [[Debajyoti Mishra]] & Deep-Loy\n| cinematography = [[Rana Dasgupta]]\n| editing        = [[Prokash Golam Mustafa]]\n| studio         = Gorai Films\n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|2020|02|03|Dhaka, Bangladesh}}\n| runtime        = 112 minutes\n| country        = [[Bangladesh]]\n| language       = [[Bengali language|Bengali]]\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \n}}\n\n'''''The Boundary''''' ({{lang-bn|\u0997\u09a3\u09cd\u09a1\u09bf}}) is a 2020 [[Bangladeshi]] drama film directed by [[Fakhrul Arefeen Khan]] and starring [[Sabyasachi Chakrabarty]], [[Suborna Mustafa]] and others.\n\n==Plot==\nRetired government official, widower, sixty up Mr. Azgar Ali lives alone with driver and working people in an elite area of Dhaka. The only child Ali Mizan lives in London with family. After two years, he comes home to see his father. Azgar Ali is suffering from dementia and living with a faint memory. His daily routine is gardening on the roof, watching stars at night, walking in the park in the morning and talking to Skype with her granddaughter, Arha, in London. Due to poor memory, Azgar Ali makes many mistakes every day. One such mistake was to transfer Tk 5 lakh to Mrs Shamira's account by mistake. Fifty up Mrs. Shamima is also a lonely person. Dentist by profession. She is the neighbor of Azgar Ali. Her only daughter lives in London with husband Jason. Azgar Ali's and Shamima was acquainted to each other, by transferring money to Shamima's account by mistake of Azgar Ali, from acquaintances they became friends. Azgar Ali's doctor advised the two to go to Cox's Bazar. Azgar Ali's son Ali Mizan, daughter in law Millie and Mrs. Shamima's daughter got to know about their outing. Within three days the son, daughter in law and daughter of Shamima arrives from London. The emotional battle of parents and children starts with Azhar Ali and Mrs Shamma after that.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Sabyasachi Chakrabarty]]\n* [[Suborna Mustafa]]\n* [[Aparna Ghose]] \n* [[Maznun Mizan]] \n\n== Production ==\nThe film was produced by Gorai Films. \n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Boundary, The (2020 film)}}\n[[Category:2020 films]]\n[[Category:2020s comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi films]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Debajyoti Mishra]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Fakhrul Arefeen Khan]]\n[[Category:2020s Bengali-language films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Bangladesh]]\n", "text_old": "{{unreferenced|date=March 2020}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = The Boundary\n| film name      = \u0997\u09a3\u09cd\u09a1\u09bf\n| image          = Gondi.jpg\n| caption        = The Boundary\n| director       = [[Fakhrul Arefeen Khan]]\n| Producer       = [[Fakhrul Arefeen Khan]] & [[Israt Sultana]]\n| writer         = [[Fakhrul Arefeen Khan]]\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Sabyasachi Chakrabarty]]\n* [[Suborna Mustafa]]\n* [[Aparna Ghose]] \n* [[Maznun Mizan]] \n}}\n| music          = [[Debajyoti Mishra]] & Deep-Loy\n| cinematography = [[Rana Dasgupta]]\n| editing        = [[Prokash Golam Mustafa]]\n| studio         = Gorai Films\n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|2020|02|03|Dhaka, Bangladesh}}\n| runtime        = 112 minutes\n| country        = [[Bangladesh]]\n| language       = [[Bengali language|Bengali]]\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \n}}\n\n'''''The Boundary''''' ({{lang-bn|\u0997\u09a3\u09cd\u09a1\u09bf}}) is a 2020 [[Bangladeshi]] drama film directed by [[Fakhrul Arefeen Khan]] and starring [[Sabyasachi Chakrabarty]], [[Suborna Mustafa]] and others.\n\n==Plot==\nRetired government official, widower, sixty up Mr. Azgar Ali lives alone with driver and working people in an elite area of Dhaka. The only child Ali Mizan lives in London with family. After two years, he comes home to see his father. Azgar Ali is suffering from dementia and living with a faint memory. His daily routine is gardening on the roof, watching stars at night, walking in the park in the morning and talking to Skype with her granddaughter, Arha, in London. Due to poor memory, Azgar Ali makes many mistakes every day. One such mistake was to transfer Tk 5 lakh to Mrs Shamira's account by mistake. Fifty up Mrs. Shamima is also a lonely person. Dentist by profession. She is the neighbor of Azgar Ali. Her only daughter lives in London with husband Jason. Azgar Ali's and Shamima was acquainted to each other, by transferring money to Shamima's account by mistake of Azgar Ali, from acquaintances they became friends. Azgar Ali's doctor advised the two to go to Cox's Bazar. Azgar Ali's son Ali Mizan, daughter in law Millie and Mrs. Shamima's daughter got to know about their outing. Within three days the son, daughter in law and daughter of Shamima arrives from London. The emotional battle of parents and children starts with Azhar Ali and Mrs Shamma after that.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Sabyasachi Chakrabarty]]\n* [[Suborna Mustafa]]\n* [[Aparna Ghose]] \n* [[Maznun Mizan]] \n\n== Production ==\nThe film was produced by Gorai Films. \n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT: The Boundary}}\n[[Category:2020 films]]\n[[Category:2020s comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi films]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Debajyoti Mishra]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Fakhrul Arefeen Khan]]\n[[Category:2020s Bengali-language films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Bangladesh]]\n", "name_user": "Bovineboy2008", "label": "safe", "comment": "fix sortkey", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Boundary_(2020_film)"}
{"title_page": "Unna Nenachen Pattu Padichen", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=November 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Unna Nenachen Pattu Padichen\n| image          = \n| image_size     =\n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Guru Dhanapal]]\n| producer       = G. D. Ramesh\n| writer         = Guru Dhanapal\n| starring       = {{ubl|[[Karthik (actor)|Karthik]]|[[Rajani (actress)|Sasikala]]|[[Monisha]]|[[Nizhalgal Ravi]]|[[Anandaraj]]|[[Janagaraj]]|[[Rajesh (actor)|Rajesh]]|[[Senthil]]|[[Vinu Chakravarthy]]|[[Vijayan (actor)|Vijayan]]}}\n| music          = [[Ilaiyaraaja]]\n| cinematography = Guru Dhanapal\n| editing        = K. R. Ramalingam\n| distributor    =\n| studio         = Sree Padmavathy Movie Makers\n| released       = {{Film date|df=y|1992|04|12}}\n| runtime        = 140 minutes\n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n}}\n\n'''''Unna Nenachen Pattu Padichen''''' is a [[Tamil films of 1992|1992]] [[Tamil language|Tamil]] [[drama film]] directed by [[Guru Dhanapal]]. The film features [[Karthik (actor)|Karthik]], [[Rajani (actress)|Sasikala]] and [[Monisha]] in lead roles. The film, produced by G. D. Ramesh, had musical score by [[Ilaiyaraaja]] and was released on 12 April 1992. The song in the film \"Ennai Thottu Alli Konda\" has a cult listening in the rural south of India and is often played repeatedly during festivals even now.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://spicyonion.com/movie/unnai-ninaichan-paatu-padichen/|title=Unnai Ninaichan Paatu Padichen (1992) Tamil Movie|accessdate=2013-04-21|publisher=spicyonion.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/tamil/movies/unna-nenachen-paattu-padicchen.html|title=Unna Nenachen Paattu Padicchen|accessdate=2013-04-21|publisher=entertainment.oneindia.in}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cinesouth.com/cgi-bin/filmography/newfilmdb.cgi?name=unnai%20nenachen%20pattu%20padichen|title=Filmography of unnai nenachen pattu padichen|accessdate=2013-04-21|publisher=cinesouth.com}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\n\nMuthurasu ([[Karthik (actor)|Karthik]]) and Periyasamy ([[Nizhalgal Ravi]]) are brothers, and live with their father ([[Vinu Chakravarthy]]) and their grandmother ([[Kanthimathi]]). Meenakshi ([[Rajani (actress)|Sasikala]]), Muthurasu's cousin, will marry another man ([[Anandaraj]]) but she must marry Muthurasu or Periyasamy as per the customs. The brothers then decide to kidnap Meenakshi. In the process, Periyasamy dies.\n\nThe two villages then clash and arrange a panchayat to solve the problem. During the panchayat, Meenakshi says that she will stay in her uncle's house because Meenakshi hates the groom. Muthurasu's father decides to arrange the marriage between Muthurasu and Meenakshi but Muthurasu cannot forget his lover Dhanam ([[Monisha]]) who died a few years ago. What transpires later forms the crux of the story.\n\n==Cast==\n{{colbegin}}\n*[[Karthik (actor)|Karthik]] as Muthurasu\n*[[Rajani (actress)|Sasikala]] as Meenakshi\n*[[Monisha]] as Dhanam\n*[[Nizhalgal Ravi]] as Periyasamy\n*[[Anandaraj]]\n*[[Janagaraj]]\n*[[Rajesh (actor)|Rajesh]]\n*[[Senthil]] as Kuppusamy\n*[[Vinu Chakravarthy]]\n*[[Vijayan (actor)|Vijayan]] as Rathnasamy, Meenakshi's father\n*[[Kanthimathi]]\n*[[P. R. Varalakshmi]] as Chinna Thayi, Dhanam's mother\n*Vijaya Chandrika as Meenakshi's mother\n*[[Kovai Sarala]] as Shanthi\n*Tiruppur Ramasamy\n*A. K. Veerasamy as Poosari\n*Karuppu Subbaiah\n*[[Periya Karuppu Thevar]]\n*Azhagu\n{{colend}}\n\n==Soundtrack==\n\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Unna Nenachen Pattu Padichen\n| type       = [[soundtrack]]\n| artist     = [[Ilaiyaraaja]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = 1992\n| recorded   = 1992\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = 25:08\n| label      =\n| producer   = [[Ilaiyaraaja]]\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n}}\n\nThe film score and the soundtrack were composed by [[film composer]] [[Ilaiyaraaja]]. The soundtrack, released in 1992, features five tracks with lyrics written by [[Vaali (poet)|Vaali]], [[Gangai Amaran]], Piraisoodan and Ponnadiyan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hummaa.com/music/album/unnai-nenachen-pattu-padichen/37181|title=Unnai Nenachen Pattu Padichen - Hummaa|accessdate=2013-04-20|publisher=hummaa.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.raaga.com/channels/tamil/album/T0000217.html|title=Unnai Nenaichen Paatu Padichen Songs|accessdate=2013-04-20|publisher=raaga.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://music.ovi.com/in/en/pc/Product/Ilaiyaraaja/Unnai-Ninaichen-Paattu-Padichen/25223884|title=Download Unnai Ninaichen Paattu Padichen by Ilaiyaraaja with Nokia Music|accessdate=2013-04-20|publisher=music.ovi.com}}</ref>\n\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#CCCCCC\" align=\"center\"\n! Track !! Song !! Singer(s) !! Duration\n|- \n|1 || 'Ennai Thottu' || [[S. P. Balasubrahmanyam]], [[Swarnalatha]] || 4:54\n|-\n|2 || 'Kanna Un Kannil' || [[Swarnalatha]] || 4:49\n|-\n|3 || 'Vaanam Idi Idikka' || S. P. Balasubrahmanyam, [[S. Janaki]] || 4:59\n|-\n|4 || 'Mundi Mundi Nayaagare' || [[Ilaiyaraaja]], [[Malaysia Vasudevan]] || 5:28\n|-\n|5 || 'Thottu Thottu Thukkipattu' || [[Minmini]] || 4:58\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|0318790|Unna Nenachen Pattu Padichen}}\n\n[[Category:1992 films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian drama films]]\n[[Category:1990s drama films]]\n[[Category:Tamil film scores by Ilaiyaraaja]]\n[[Category:1990s Tamil-language films]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=November 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Unna Nenachen Pattu Padichen\n| image          = \n| image_size     =\n| caption        = 