 a [[Fusilier]] and a [[Coldstream Guards|Coldstream Guard]]; the crowning figure represents Honour. They are cast in bronze from cannon captured at the [[Siege of Sevastopol (1854\u20131855)|Siege of Sevastopol]].<ref>{{Harvnb|Ward-Jackson|2011|pp=388\u201390}}</ref>\n| designation = {{sort|C|[https://www.historicengland.org.uk/listing/the-list/list-entry/1066141 Grade II]}}\n}}\n{{Public art row\n| image       = The Boy, St James\u2019s Park.jpg\n| subject     = {{sort|Boy|''The Boy''}}\n| commonscat  = The Greek Boy Fountain, 1863, by Lady von Gleichen\n| type        = Drinking fountain with sculpture\n| location    = St James's Park\n| coordinates = {{coord|51.5012|-0.1341|format=dms|type:landmark_region:GB-WSM}}\n| date        = 1863\n| artist      = {{sortname|Charles Henry|Mabey|nolink=1}} <small>for Robert Jackson & Son</small>\n| architect   = {{n/a}}\n| notes       = A marble figure of a boy naked to the waist, set on a granite plinth with marble panels. The badly worn and much vandalised sculpture was repaired in 1993 and unveiled by [[Douglas Hurd]].<ref>{{Harvnb|Ward-Jackson|2011|p=240}}</ref>\n| designation = {{sort|C|[https://www.historicengland.org.uk/listing/the-list/list-entry/1235671 Grade II]}}\n}}\n{{Public art row\n| image       = John Franklin statue.jpg\n| subject     = {{sort|Franklin|Statue of [[John&nbsp;Franklin]]}}\n| commonscat  = Statue of John Franklin, London\n| type        = Statue\n| location    = Waterloo Place\n| coordinates = {{coord|51.5064|-0.1322|format=dms|type:landmark_region:GB-WSM}}\n| date        = 1866\n| artist      = {{sortname|Matthew|Noble}}\n| architect   = {{n/a}}\n| notes       = Unveiled 15 November 1866. Franklin is depicted in the act of announcing the discovery of the [[Northwest Passage]] to his officers and crew. At the back of the pedestal is a map of the Arctic, showing the positions of the boats and crews at the moment of Franklin's burial.<ref>{{Harvnb|Ward-Jackson|2011|pp=390\u201392}}</ref>\n| designa