eau Brummell Statue Jermyn Street.JPG\n| subject     = {{sort|Brummel|Statue of [[Beau&nbsp;Brummell]]}}\n| commonscat  = Statue of Beau Brummell, London\n| type        = Statue\n| location    = [[Jermyn Street]]\n| coordinates = {{coord|51.507700|-0.138900|format=dms|type:landmark_region:GB-WSM}}\n| date        = 2002\n| artist      = {{sortname|Irena|Sedleck\u00e1}}\n| architect   = {{n/a}}\n| notes       = Unveiled 5 November 2002 by [[Princess Michael of Kent]]. Sedleck\u00e1 originally conceived the sculpture for the Bond Street site now occupied by Lawrence Holofcener's ''Allies''.<ref>{{Harvnb|Ward-Jackson|2011|pp=105\u201306}}</ref>\n| designation = {{n/a}}\n}}\n{{Public art row\n| image       = The National Police Memorial - geograph.org.uk - 1568965.jpg\n| subject     = {{sort|National Police Memorial|[[National Police Memorial (United Kingdom)|National Police Memorial]]}} | commonscat  =National Police Memorial, London\n| type        = Memorial with stele\n| location    = [[The Mall, London|The Mall]], in front of the [[Admiralty Citadel]]\n| coordinates = {{coord|51.505742|-0.130064|format=dms|type:landmark_region:GB-WSM}}\n| date        = 2005\n| artist      = {{sortname|Per|Arnoldi}}\n| architect   = [[Foster and Partners]]\n| notes       = Unveiled 26 April 2005 by Elizabeth II. The memorial incorporates a ventilation shaft for the [[London Underground]], faced with black granite and containing a Roll of Honour.<ref>{{Harvnb|Ward-Jackson|2011|pp=144\u201345}}</ref>\n| designation = {{n/a}}\n}}\n{{Public art row\n| image       = Queen mother statue.jpg\n| subject     = {{sort|Elizabeth|[[George VI and Queen Elizabeth Memorial|Statue]] of [[Queen&nbsp;Elizabeth The&nbsp;Queen Mother]]}}\n| commonscat  = George VI and Queen Elizabeth Monument\n| type        = Memorial with statue and relief sculpture\n| location    = [[The Mall, London|The Mall]]\n| coordinates = {{coord|51.505128|-0.133716|format=dms|type:landmark_region:GB-WSM}}\n| date        = 2009\n