ect   = {{sortname|Eric|Parry}} Architects\n| type        = Architectural sculpture\n| designation = {{n/a}}\n| notes       = Unveiled 6 March 2013.<ref name=\"Welch 2013\">{{citation|url=https://www.e-architect.co.uk/london/one-eagle-place-development|title=One Eagle Place Development, Piccadilly|first=Adrian|last=Welch|publisher=e-architect|date=14 June 2013|accessdate=3 February 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Public art row\n| image       = Simon Milton (27346128435).jpg\n| subject     = {{sort|Milton|Bust of [[Simon&nbsp;Milton (politician)|Simon&nbsp;Milton]]}}\n| location    = One Eagle Place (Corner of Piccadilly and Eagle Place)\n| date        = 2013\n| artist      = {{sortname|Alan|Micklethwaite|nolink=yes}}\n| architect   = \n| type        = Architectural sculpture\n| designation =\n| notes       = Unveiled by [[Boris Johnson]], [[Mayor of London]]; Milton was a [[Deputy Mayor of London|Deputy Mayor]] before his death in 2011 aged 49.<ref>{{citation|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/london/sculpture-honour-for-deputy-mayor-sir-simon-milton-8594329.html|title=Sculpture honour for deputy mayor Sir Simon Milton|first=Ross|last=Lydall|date=29 April 2013|publisher=Evening Standard|accessdate=3 February 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Public art row\n| image       = Architectural sculpture, One Eagle Place.jpg\n| subject     = Architectural sculpture\n| type        = Architectural sculpture\n| location    = One Eagle Place (Corner of Eagle Place and Jermyn Street)\n| date        = 2013\n| artist      = {{sortname|Stephen|Cox|dab=sculptor}}\n| architect   = {{sortname|Eric|Parry}} Architects\n| designation = {{n/a}}\n| notes       = Unveiled 13 June 2013.<ref name=\"Welch 2013\"/>\n}}\n{{Public art row\n| image       = Edwin Lutyens memorial.jpg\n| subject     = ''Relief: Figure Emerging'' and ''{{nowrap|Inscribed Rail to E.L.}}''<br><small>[[Edwin Lutyens]]</small>\n| location    = Apple Tree Yard (rear of 8 [[St James's Square]])\n| date        = 2014\u201315\n| artist      = {{sor