ringham]], Norfolk.<ref>{{Harvnb|Ward-Jackson|2011|pp=143\u201344}}</ref>\n| designation = {{n/a}}\n}}\n{{Public art row\n| image       = Memorial to Yvonne Fletcher.JPG\n| subject     = {{sort|Fletcher|Memorial to {{nobreak|[[Murder of Yvonne Fletcher|Yvonne Fletcher]]}}}}\n| commonscat  = WPC Yvonne Fletcher memorial, St. James's Square\n| type        = Stele\n| location    = [[St James's Square]]\n| coordinates = {{coord|51.507681|-0.135057|format=dms|type:landmark_region:GB-WSM}}\n| date        = 1985\n| artist      = {{sortname|George|Cook|nolink=1}} and Rosemary Slinn\n| architect   = {{n/a}}\n| notes       = Unveiled 1 February 1985 by [[Margaret Thatcher]]. The first memorial to be erected by the [[Police Memorial Trust]], founded in response to Fletcher's shooting during a siege of the Libyan embassy on the Square.<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.policerollofhonour.org.uk/memorial/memorial_trust/pmt.htm |title=Police Memorial Trust |work=National Police Officers Roll of Honour |accessdate=11 December 2012}}</ref><ref>{{citation|url=https://www.iwm.org.uk/memorials/item/memorial/59074|title=WPC Yvonne Fletcher \u2013 Stone of Remembrance|work=War Memorials Register|publisher=Imperial War Museums|accessdate=27 May 2019}}</ref>\n| designation = {{n/a}}\n}}\n{{Public art row\n| image       = Moonlight Ramble (4869644059).jpg\n| subject     = ''Moonlight Ramble''\n| location    = Haymarket House, 27 Haymarket\n| date        = 1992\n| artist      = {{sortname|Jane|Ackroyd}}\n| architect   =\n| type        =\n| designation =\n| notes       = {{sfn|Ward-Jackson|2011|p=64}}\n}}\n{{Public art row\n| image       = General de Gaulle - geograph.org.uk - 717956.jpg\n| subject     = {{sort|Gaulle|Statue of [[Charles de Gaulle]]}}\n| commonscat  = Statue of Charles de Gaulle, London\n| type        = Statue\n| location    = Carlton Gardens\n| coordinates = {{coord|51.505650|-0.134200|format=dms|type:landmark_region:GB-WSM}}\n| date        = 1993\n| artist      = {{sortname|A