onour-for-deputy-mayor-sir-simon-milton-8594329.html|title=Sculpture honour for deputy mayor Sir Simon Milton|first=Ross|last=Lydall|date=29 April 2013|publisher=Evening Standard|accessdate=3 February 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Public art row\n| image       = Architectural sculpture, One Eagle Place.jpg\n| subject     = Architectural sculpture\n| type        = Architectural sculpture\n| location    = One Eagle Place (Corner of Eagle Place and Jermyn Street)\n| date        = 2013\n| artist      = {{sortname|Stephen|Cox|dab=sculptor}}\n| architect   = {{sortname|Eric|Parry}} Architects\n| designation = {{n/a}}\n| notes       = Unveiled 13 June 2013.<ref name=\"Welch 2013\"/>\n}}\n{{Public art row\n| image       = Edwin Lutyens memorial.jpg\n| subject     = ''Relief: Figure Emerging'' and ''{{nowrap|Inscribed Rail to E.L.}}''<br><small>[[Edwin Lutyens]]</small>\n| location    = Apple Tree Yard (rear of 8 [[St James's Square]])\n| date        = 2014\u201315\n| artist      = {{sortname|Stephen|Cox|dab=sculptor}}\n| architect   = {{sortname|Eric|Parry}}\n| type        = Relief and inscription\n| designation = {{n/a}}\n| notes       = <ref>{{citation|url=http://www.lutyenstrust.org.uk/portfolio-item/apple-tree-yard-sculpture-honours-spirit-lutyens/|title=Apple Tree Yard Sculpture Honours Spirit of Lutyens|first=Stephen|last=Cox|publisher=The Lutyens Trust|accessdate=27 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{citation|url=https://www.royalacademy.org.uk/article/stephen-cox-ra-and-eric-parry-ra|title=Stephen Cox RA and Eric Parry RA: set in stone|first=Sam|last=Phillips|publisher=Royal Academy|date=21 May 2015|accessdate=27 April 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Public art row\n| subject     = Encaustic tile panels\n| location    = St James's Market\n| date        = 2016\n| artist      = {{sortname|David|Thorpe|dab=artist}}\n| architect   =\n| type        = Encaustic tile panels\n| designation = {{n/a}}\n| notes       = <ref name=\"AAS\">{{citation|url=https://aasarchitecture.com/2016/11/public-artworks-launched-st-jamess-market-studio-weave.html/|title=Public Artworks Launched at St James\u2019s Market by Studio Weave|date=9 November 2016|website=aasarchitecture|accessdate=1 April 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Public art row\n| subject     = ''Shirt'', ''Tie'', ''Pipe'' and ''Shoe''\n| location    = St James's Market\n| date        = 2016\n| artist      = Studio Swine\n| architect   =\n| type        = Sculptural benches\n| designation = {{n/a}}\n| notes       = <ref name=\"AAS\"/>\n}}\n{{Public art row\n| image       = St James's Market (33803506735).jpg\n| subject     = ''The Safe Deposite''\n| location    = St James's Market\n| date        = 2016\n| artist      = Studio Weave\n| architect   =\n| type        = Pavilion\n| designation = {{n/a}}\n| notes       = <ref name=\"AAS\"/>\n}}\n{{Public art row\n| image       = Medaillon John Nash.JPG\n| subject     = {{sort|Nash|Relief of [[John&nbsp;Nash (architect)|John&nbsp;Nash]]}}\n| type        = Relief\n| location    = Nash Summer House, [[St James's Square]]\n| date        = {{dunno}}\n| artist      = {{sort|Couriquer (after)|After Joseph Anton Couriguer}}\n| architect   = {{sortname|John|Nash|nolink=yes}}\n| designation = {{sort|C|[https://historicengland.org.uk/listing/the-list/list-entry/1235856 Grade II]}}\n| notes       = <ref>{{citation|url=https://www.londonremembers.com/memorials/nash-summer-house-sw1|title=Bust: Nash summer house \u2013 SW1|website=London Remembers|accessdate=7 March 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Public art row\n| image       = Palmerston portrait plaque, Pickering Place.jpg\n| subject     = {{sort|Palmerston|Relief of [[Henry John Temple, 3rd Viscount Palmerston]]}}\n| type        = Relief\n| location    = Pickering Place\n| date        = {{dunno}}\n| artist      = {{dunno}}\n| architect   = {{n/a}}\n| notes       =<ref>{{citation|title=Bust: Relief bust \u2013 Palmerston|url=http://www.londonremembers.com/memorials/relief-bust-palmerston|website=London Remembers|accessdate=11 August 2014}}</ref>\n| designation = {{n/a}}\n}}\n{{Public art footer}}\n\n==Royal Institute of Painters in Water Colours==\n{{Main|Royal Institute of Painters in Water Colours}}\n{{Public art header|show_architect=yes|show_material=no|show_dimensions=no|show_owner=no}}\n{{Public art row\n| image       = Bust of Peter de Wint, Piccadilly (cropped).jpg\n| subject     = {{sort|De Wint|[[Peter De Wint]]}}\n| location    = Royal Institute of Painters in Water Colours, Piccadilly\n| artist      = {{sortname|Edward Onslow|Ford}}\n| architect   = {{sortname|Edward Robert|Robson}}\n| type        = Bust\n| designation = {{sort|C|[https://www.historicengland.org.uk/listing/the-list/list-entry/1265805 Grade II]}}\n| notes       = <ref name=\"Speel Piccadilly\"/>\n|\n}}\n{{Public art row\n| image       =\n| subject     = {{sort|Cozens|[[John Robert Cozens]]}}\n| location    = Royal Institute of Painters in Water Colours, Piccadilly\n| architect   = {{sortname|Edward Robert|Robson}}\n| type        = Bust\n| designation = {{sort|C|[https://www.historicengland.org.uk/listing/the-list/list-entry/1265805 Grade II]}}\n| artist      = {{sortname|Edward Onslow|Ford}}\n| notes       = <ref name=\"Speel Piccadilly\"/>\n|\n}}\n{{Public art row\n| image       =\n| subject     = {{sort|Cox|[[David Cox (artist)|David Cox]]}}\n| location    = Royal Institute of Painters in Water Colours, Piccadilly\n| architect   = {{sortname|Edward Robert|Robson}}\n| type        = Bust\n| designation = {{sort|C|[https://www.historicengland.org.uk/listing/the-list/list-entry/1265805 Grade II]}}\n| artist      = {{sortname|Edward Onslow|Ford}}\n| notes       = <ref name=\"Speel Piccadilly\"/>\n|\n}}\n{{Public art row\n| image       =\n| subject     = {{sort|Sandby|[[Paul Sandby]]}}\n| location    = Royal Institute of Painters in Water Colours, Piccadilly\n| architect   = {{sortname|Edward Robert|Robson}}\n| type        = Bust\n| designation = {{sort|C|[https://www.historicengland.org.uk/listing/the-list/list-entry/1265805 Grade II]}}\n| artist 