tra.com/news/local/govt-and-politics/utah-congressman-ben-mcadams-says-he-tested-positive-for-covid/article_b9b040dc-9d52-5fb0-853d-afa6040f9987.html|title=Utah Congressman Ben McAdams says he tested positive for COVID-19|last=Herald|first=Connor Richards Daily|website=Daily Herald|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319083543/https://www.heraldextra.com/news/local/govt-and-politics/utah-congressman-ben-mcadams-says-he-tested-positive-for-covid/article_b9b040dc-9d52-5fb0-853d-afa6040f9987.html|archive-date=March 19, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n====March 19====\n3,000 doctors and medical workers sign a letter asking [[U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement|ICE]] to release individuals and families detained for immigration violations, noting the harsh, overcrowded conditions are ripe for the propagation of the coronavirus.<ref>[https://news.yahoo.com/coronavirus-us-doctors-demand-immediate-093956554.html Coronavirus: US doctors demand immediate release of prisoners and detainees to avert disaster] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320195214/https://news.yahoo.com/coronavirus-us-doctors-demand-immediate-093956554.html |date=March 20, 2020 }} by Andrew Naughtie, The Independent, 19 Mar 2020</ref>\n* California: The state has ordered the closure of all museums, malls and other all non-essential workplaces effective March 20 11:59&nbsp;p.m.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/california-issues-statewide-stay-home-order-coronavirus-fight-n1164471 |title=Archived copy |access-date=March 20, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320092203/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/california-issues-statewide-stay-home-order-coronavirus-fight-n1164471 |archive-date=March 20, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> All 40 million citizens in the state are ordered to stay home. More than 900 state residents have been infected and 19 have died.<ref>[https://thehill.com/homenews/state-watch/48857