8/https://www.abc27.com/news/local/pa-department-of-education-cancels-statewide-assessments/|archive-date=March 19, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://philadelphia.cbslocal.com/2020/03/19/coronavirus-in-pennsylvania-52-new-covid-19-cases-reported-in-state-bringing-total-to-196/|title=Coronavirus In Pennsylvania: All Non-Life-Sustaining Businesses Ordered To Close Physical Locations As COVID-19 Cases Climb To 196|date=2020-03-19|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319214511/https://philadelphia.cbslocal.com/2020/03/19/coronavirus-in-pennsylvania-52-new-covid-19-cases-reported-in-state-bringing-total-to-196/|archive-date=March 19, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Tom Wolf|Governor Wolf]] ordered a statewide shutdown of \"non-life sustaining businesses\" by 8 p.m. Enforcement of this order is planned to begin at 12:01&nbsp;a.m. Saturday, March 21.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abc27.com/news/health/coronavirus/gov-wolf-officially-orders-the-closure-of-non-life-sustaining-businesses-statewide/|title=Gov. Wolf officially orders the closure of 'non-life sustaining businesses' statewide|date=2020-03-19|website=ABC27|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320181119/https://www.abc27.com/news/health/coronavirus/gov-wolf-officially-orders-the-closure-of-non-life-sustaining-businesses-statewide/|archive-date=March 20, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*South Carolina: Governor McMaster issued new executive order to keep more people on home, all non-essential state employees to [[Stay-at-home order|stay at home]]. Public universities are also encouraged to finish the semester online. 81 cases are confirmed on the state.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thestate.com/news/coronavirus/article241298056.html|title=21 new cases of coronavirus found in SC. Abbeville, Saluda counties see first cases|last=Bohatch|first=Emily|date=19 March 2020|website=The State|url-status=live|archiv