 cops quarantined|first1=Ryan|last1=Miller|first2=Marco|last2=Cava|date=March 20, 2020|website=usatoday.com|access-date=March 21, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321020308/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/health/2020/03/20/coronavirus-updates-us-deaths-cases-stay-home-order-trump/2880695001/|archive-date=March 21, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n*California: Los Angeles Mayor [[Eric Garcetti]] promised that no one will go to jail for violating the [[stay-at-home order]] that goes into effect at midnight. However, a major purpose of the order is to provide enforcement for businesses which are not complying.<ref>\"[https://deadline.com/2020/03/los-angeles-mayor-shutdown-enforcement-order-eric-garcetti-lapd-1202888219/ L.A. Mayor Promises 'People Aren't Going To Be Marched Into Jail' Under New Safer At Home Order] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320200928/https://deadline.com/2020/03/los-angeles-mayor-shutdown-enforcement-order-eric-garcetti-lapd-1202888219/ |date=March 20, 2020 }}\" by Dominic Patten, ''Deadline'', March 20, 2020</ref> Marijuana dispensaries are classified \"essential\".<ref>[https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/20/us/la-marijuana-coronavirus-trnd/index.html Marijuana dispensaries are deemed 'essential' in LA, allowed to stay open during coronavirus order] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321025617/https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/20/us/la-marijuana-coronavirus-trnd/index.html |date=March 21, 2020 }} By Allen Kim, CNN, 20 Mar 2020</ref>\n*Illinois: Governor [[J.B. Pritzker]] issued a stay-at-home order. The order will become effective March 21 and will remain in place until April 7 but could go longer.<ref>[https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/coronavirus-illinois-issue-stay-home-order-13-million-residents-california-n1164901?fbclid=IwAR0hnei6UFmSAf_aiG9deV6sjuK8LQqcB9T1s8mpqSQHe7WR3ILy0pluCZU Coronavirus: Illinois issues stay-at-home order for 13 million residents] By Minyvonne Burke, NBC News, 20 Mar 2020</ref>\n*New York: Governor [[Andrew Cuomo]] issued a state-wide order that all non-essential workers must stay at home. He noted that the number of coronavirus cases in the state had gone from zero on March 4 to over 2,900.<ref name=deadline>\"[https://deadline.com/2020/03/new-york-stay-at-home-order-andrew-cuomo-1202888587/ New York Governor Issues Statewide Stay-At-Home Order For All Non-Essential Workers] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320170143/https://deadline.com/2020/03/new-york-stay-at-home-order-andrew-cuomo-1202888587/ |date=March 20, 2020 }}\" by Erik Pederson, ''Deadline'', March 20, 2020</ref> The same day, Coronavirus cases in New York exceed 7000.<ref name=CNN>\"[https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/20/politics/new-york-workforce-stay-home/index.html] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320204137/https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/20/politics/new-york-workforce-stay-home/index.html |date=March 20, 2020 }}\" by Veronica Stracqualursi, ''CNN'', March 20, 2020</ref>\n*Michigan: The state reports 225 new cases of coronavirus, bringing the total number of cases there to 549.<ref>{{cite web |title=Michigan coronavirus (COVID-19) cases continue to rise, state total now 549 |url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/health/2020/03/20/michigan-coronavirus-covid-19-cases-continue-to-rise-state-total-now-549/ |website=clickondetroit.com |accessdate=20 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320203728/https://www.clickondetroit.com/health/2020/03/20/michigan-coronavirus-covid-19-cases-continue-to-rise-state-total-now-549/ |archive-date=March 20, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Also, a fourth death from coronavirus is reported, a man in his 50s from Oakland County who had underlying health conditions.<ref>{{cite web |title=Officials say Oakland County man is 4th person to die from coronavirus in Michigan |url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/news/local/2020/03/21/officials-say-oakland-county-man-is-4th-person-to-die-from-coronavirus-in-michigan/ |website=clickondetroit.com |accessdate=21 March 2020}}</ref>\n*North Carolina: The state activated [[North Carolina National Guard]] to assist in logistics and transportation of medical supplies, as the state reported it had 179 cases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newsobserver.com/news/coronavirus/article241363186.html|title=As coronavirus keeps spreading across NC, National Guard activated and citizens stock up|last=Quillin|first=Martha|date=20 March 2020|website=The News & Observer|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320190055/https://www.newsobserver.com/news/coronavirus/article241363186.html|archive-date=March 20, 2020|access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n*Ohio: The state reported its first coronavirus death, Mark Wagoner Sr, a 76-year-old attorney from [[Lucas County, Ohio|Lucas County]] in the [[Toledo, Ohio|Toledo]] area.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.10tv.com/article/dewine-says-1st-ohio-coronavirus-death-76-year-old-man-2020-mar|title=DeWine says 1st Ohio coronavirus death is 76-year-old man|date=March 20, 2020|website=10tv.com|access-date=March 21, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321014412/https://www.10tv.com/article/dewine-says-1st-ohio-coronavirus-death-76-year-old-man-2020-mar|archive-date=March 21, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The state had a total of 169 cases. Governor DeWine announces that senior centers and senior daycare centers will close.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nbc4i.com/community/coronavirus-in-ohio-governor-odh-plan-friday-afternoon-update/|title=Coronavirus in Ohio Friday update: 169 cases, first death confirmed|date=March 20, 2020|website=nbc4i.com|access-date=March 21, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321015231/https://www.nbc4i.com/community/coronavirus-in-ohio-governor-odh-plan-friday-afternoon-update/|archive-date=March 21, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*Tennessee: 15 recovery cases are confirmed in [[Nashville, Tennessee|Nashville]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=ht