: The state announced that it had 65 confirmed coronavirus cases.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.newsobserver.com/news/coronavirus/article241238276.html |title=Coronavirus live updates: Here's what to know in North Carolina on March 17 |last=Simone |first=Jasper |date=17 March 2020 |website=The News & Observer |url-status=live |access-date=17 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317163612/https://www.newsobserver.com/news/coronavirus/article241238276.html |archive-date=March 17, 2020 }}</ref> The state also announced that it had run 1,100 tests.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Murphy |first=Brian |url=https://www.newsobserver.com/news/coronavirus/article241270931.html |title=More than 1,100 coronavirus tests have been run, and NC is prepping for more |date=17 March 2020 |work=The News & Observer |url-status=live |access-date=March 18, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318174607/https://www.newsobserver.com/news/coronavirus/article241270931.html |archive-date=March 18, 2020 }}</ref>\n* Ohio: The state had 67 confirmed cases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://abc6onyourside.com/news/local/march-17-coronavirus-in-ohio-update|title=67 confirmed coronavirus cases in Ohio, 17 people hospitalized|first=Lu Ann|last=Stoia|date=March 17, 2010|website=abc6onyourside.com|access-date=March 18, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317200446/https://abc6onyourside.com/news/local/march-17-coronavirus-in-ohio-update|archive-date=March 17, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Governor DeWine orders that elective surgeries be postponed.<ref name= \"CBS10 TIMELINE\"/>\n*Pennsylvania: All liquor stores closed indefinitely.<ref>[https://edition.cnn.com/world/live-news/coronavirus-outbreak-03-16-20-intl-hnk/h_6e1f01640b115ad8c8c625f496fd06a5?fbclid=IwAR34M94sJN_64OBSI90MNjOkjhlJMxMX6c69pUluy-BwjnGaOr_fO1Vgx6A Pennsylvania closes all state liquor stores indefinitely] By Ben Westcott, Helen Regan, Adam Renton, Meg Wagner and Veronica Rocha, CNN, March 17, 2020</ref