.com/police-north-carolina-stopped-truck-003300973.html |date=March 20, 2020 }} by Rosie Perper, INSIDER, 19 Mar 2020</ref>\n* Ohio: The state has 119 cases of COVID-19 resulting in 33 hospitalizations.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nbc4i.com/community/health/coronavirus/coronavirus-in-ohio-thursday-update-governer-odh-to-give-afternoon-update-on-covid-19/|title=Coronavirus in Ohio Thursday update: 119 confirmed cases in the state|date=March 19, 2020|website=nbc4i.com|access-date=March 20, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320003405/https://www.nbc4i.com/community/health/coronavirus/coronavirus-in-ohio-thursday-update-governer-odh-to-give-afternoon-update-on-covid-19/|archive-date=March 20, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Governor DeWine signs state active duty proclamation that will activate 300 personnel from the [[Ohio National Guard]] to help with humanitarian efforts.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news5cleveland.com/news/continuing-coverage/coronavirus/gov-dewine-activates-300-personnel-from-ohio-national-guard-to-assist-with-local-food-distribution|title=Gov. DeWine activates 300 personnel from Ohio National Guard to assist with local food distribution|first=Kaylyn|last=Hlavaty|date=March 19, 2020|website=news5cleveland.com|access-date=March 21, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320132810/https://www.news5cleveland.com/news/continuing-coverage/coronavirus/gov-dewine-activates-300-personnel-from-ohio-national-guard-to-assist-with-local-food-distribution|archive-date=March 20, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> \n* Pennsylvania: The state's [[Pennsylvania Department of Education|department of education]] announced that all statewide assessments would be canceled for the remainder of the 2019\u20132020 school year. Pennsylvania has a current total of 196 coronavirus cases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abc27.com/news/local/pa-department-of-education-cancels-statewide-assessments/|title=Pa. Department of Education cancels statewide assess